## Component Organization

Components inside a page directory are colocated with their page. They are peers of the page component — they change together.

```
// ✅ — colocated, changed together
src/pages/configure/CombinationForm.tsx
src/pages/configure/PrinterSelector.tsx
src/pages/configure/availability.ts

// ❌ — no features/ directory
src/features/configure/components/CombinationForm.tsx
```

A component moves to `src/shared/` only when it has zero domain knowledge. `SegmentedSelector` receives `options` and `value` — it does not know what materials are. `SearchableDropdown` receives an `items` array — it does not know what printers are. Domain binding happens in `MaterialSelector.tsx` and `PrinterSelector.tsx`.

If a component is only used in one place and contains product logic, it stays in its page directory. The refactor to shared is cheap when the time comes.

---

## File Naming

| What | Convention |
|---|---|
| Page components | `PascalCase.tsx` (`ConfigurePage.tsx`) |
| Feature components | `PascalCase.tsx` (`CombinationForm.tsx`) |
| Shared components | `PascalCase.tsx` (`SegmentedSelector.tsx`) |
| Hooks | `use` + `PascalCase.ts` — add under `src/hooks/` when shared |
| Pure utilities | `camelCase.ts` (`slug.ts`, `url-params.ts`, `manifest.ts`) |
| Non-UI modules | `camelCase.ts` (`availability.ts`, `importGuides.ts`) |
| Tests | `<filename>.test.ts(x)` colocated |
| Types file | `types.ts` (singular, at `src/types.ts`) |

---

## What Does NOT Exist at MVP

This is a hard list. If an agent suggests any of the following, it is out of scope.

| Pattern | Why it does not exist |
|---|---|
| `src/features/` | The project uses `src/pages/` — approved in `folder-structure.md` |
| `src/hooks/` | No shared hooks yet; manifest and feedback are handled inline |
| `src/store/` | No global store; Zustand is not installed |
| `src/types/` directory | `src/types.ts` is a single file by explicit architectural decision |
| `@tanstack/react-query` | Not installed; plain `fetch` is sufficient at MVP |
| `SlicerOverride.tsx` | Cut at MVP — slicer format is derived from printer |
| `Button.tsx` / `Card.tsx` in shared | Not built; CSS utility classes in `global.css` at MVP |
| Storybook | Not in the spec; not in any story |
| `api.ts` per page/feature | One direct `fetch` call does not require an abstraction layer |
| `src/lib/httpClient.ts` | Not needed; plain `fetch` is sufficient |
| `POST /api/generate` | Client-side slug construction replaces it |
| `GET /api/profile/:slug/stats` | Deferred post-launch — static confidence message at MVP |
| `forwardRef` | React 19 — `ref` is a prop |

